#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:178
msgid "**Issue 1 — Session token extraction from `/connect` (fixed)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:180
msgid ""
"The spec defines the `/connect` response as returning the session token via "
"a `Set-Cookie` header, not `X-DM-DST`. The security scheme confirms that `X-"
"DM-DST` is the header used on _subsequent requests_, with the note that the "
"token value is found under \"HEADERS\" in the connect response. The `private "
"async connect()` method in `edocs.service.ts` was updated to parse `Set-"
"Cookie` and handle both the cookie-value format and a direct `X-DM-DST` "
"header as a fallback, covering any server-side variation between eDOCS "
"versions."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:182
msgid ""
"private async connect(): Promise<void> {\n"
"  // ...\n"
"  const response = await this.client.post('/connect', {\n"
"    data: {\n"
"      userid: config.edocs.userId,\n"
"      password: config.edocs.password,\n"
"      library: config.edocs.library,\n"
"    },\n"
"  });\n"
"\n"
"  // The spec returns the session token as Set-Cookie on /connect.\n"
"  // Extract the token value from the first cookie.\n"
"  const setCookie = response.headers['set-cookie'];\n"
"  const cookieHeader = Array.isArray(setCookie) ? setCookie[0] : setCookie;\n"
"  const token = cookieHeader?.split(';')[0]?.split('=').slice(1).join('=') "
"?? undefined;\n"
"\n"
"  if (!token) {\n"
"    throw new Error(\n"
"      'eDOCS connect() succeeded but no session token found in Set-Cookie "
"response header'\n"
"    );\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  this.sessionToken = token;\n"
"  logger.info('Connected to eDOCS — session token cached');\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:211
msgid ""
"**Issue 2 — `_restapi.ref` for workspace linking in document upload "
"(unverified)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:213
msgid ""
"The `UploadData` schema in the spec only documents `_restapi: { form_name: "
"\"...\" }`. The `ref` object used to link an uploaded document to a "
"workspace (`_restapi.ref.type = \"workspace\"`) is documented for the `/"
"urls` endpoint but not explicitly for `/documents`. It is expected to work "
"in practice — this is a known eDOCS REST API pattern — but must be confirmed "
"against a live DOCUVITT server when credentials become available."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:215
msgid "**Issue 3 — `CollectionResponse` shape (no action required)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:217
msgid ""
"The spec defines `CollectionResponse → data → { set: {...}, list: [...] }`. "
"The service correctly navigates this as `response.data?.data?.list`, where "
"the outer `.data` is the HTTP response body and the inner `.data.list` "
"follows the spec's structure."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:221
msgid "Switching to live mode (DOCUVITT)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:223
msgid ""
"No code changes are required. Switching to a live eDOCS server is purely a "
"configuration change."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:225
msgid "1. Set the environment variables on Azure App Service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:227
msgid ""
"az webapp config appsettings set \\\n"
"  --name ronl-business-api-acc \\\n"
"  --resource-group rg-ronl-acc \\\n"
"  --settings \\\n"
"    EDOCS_BASE_URL=\"https://<docuvitt-host>/edocsapi/v1.0\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_LIBRARY=\"DOCUVITT\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_USER_ID=\"<user-id-from-credentials>\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_PASSWORD=\"<password-from-credentials>\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_STUB_MODE=\"false\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:239
msgid "Do not put these values in any `.env` file in the repository."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:241
msgid "2. Restart the App Service"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:243
msgid ""
"Azure restarts the App Service automatically when Application settings are "
"saved. Confirm the slot is back up:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:245
msgid ""
"az webapp show \\\n"
"  --name ronl-business-api-acc \\\n"
"  --resource-group rg-ronl-acc \\\n"
"  --query \"state\" \\\n"
"  --output tsv"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:253
msgid "Then confirm the application itself is healthy:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:255
msgid "curl -s https://acc.api.open-regels.nl/v1/health | jq .data.status"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:259
msgid ""
"`Running` from Azure confirms the process started. `\"healthy\"` from the "
"health endpoint confirms Express is bound and all dependencies are reachable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:261
msgid "3. Verify the switch"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:263
msgid ""
"TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n"
"  https://acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl/realms/ronl/protocol/openid-connect/"
"token \\\n"
"  -H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" \\\n"
"  -d \"grant_type=client_credentials\" \\\n"
"  -d \"client_id=copilot-studio-edocs\" \\\n"
"  -d \"client_secret=<current-secret>\" \\\n"
"  | jq -r .access_token)\n"
"\n"
"curl -s https://acc.api.open-regels.nl/v1/edocs/status \\\n"
"  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" | jq ."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:276
msgid ""
"`status` should now be `\"up\"` and `stubMode` should be `false`. A `502` "
"response means `EDOCS_BASE_URL` or the credentials are incorrect."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:278
msgid "4. Rotate the Keycloak client secret"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:280
msgid ""
"Once real DOCUVITT credentials are active, the existing client secret must "
"be rotated:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:282
msgid ""
"Keycloak admin console on ACC → Clients → `copilot-studio-edocs` → "
"Credentials → **Regenerate**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:283
msgid "Update the Copilot Studio connector with the new secret"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:285
msgid "5. Repeat for production when ready"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:287
msgid ""
"az webapp config appsettings set \\\n"
"  --name ronl-business-api-prod \\\n"
"  --resource-group rg-ronl-prod \\\n"
"  --settings \\\n"
"    EDOCS_BASE_URL=\"https://<docuvitp-host>/edocsapi/v1.0\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_LIBRARY=\"DOCUVITP\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_USER_ID=\"<user-id-from-credentials>\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_PASSWORD=\"<password-from-credentials>\" \\\n"
"    EDOCS_STUB_MODE=\"false\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:299
msgid "And rotate the client secret on `keycloak.open-regels.nl` as in step 4."
msgstr ""
